flag
Homonym Number:  3
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an old word for any of a number of rushes; bulrush, raupo, cooper's flag


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1930-1950 Still in occasional use in Marlborough and Wellington (HWO, N.C. Small) with the more common <i>raupo, bulrush</i>.
Citations
